{"cursor":"20487","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox musical artist| \n| name = Steve \"Silk\" Hurley image = Steve \"Silk\" Hurley.jpg caption =\n| image_size = background = non_performing_personnel birth_name = Steven Hurley\n| alias = Steve Hurley, Jack Master Silk, The Voices of Life, SilkMix.com\n| birth_date = death_date = origin = Chicago, Illinois, USA instrument = genre =\n| House occupation = DJ, record producer, remixer, Singer-songwriter\n| years_active = 1985âpresent label = RCA, Silk Entertainment, Atlantic,\n| InDaSoul, Underground associated_acts = Silk & The Soul Crew, In Da Soul, The\n| Reunion Project website = [http://www.myspace.com Steve \"Silk\" Hurley]\n| current_members = past_members = notable_instruments =\n}}\n\n'Steve \"Silk\" Hurley' (born 'Steven Hurley' on November 9, 1962, Chicago,\nIllinois, USA) is an American club DJ, pioneering house-music producer,\nsongwriter, and four time Grammy Award-nominee. Two times as Remixer of the\nYear, Non-Classical (in 1999 and 2000), respectively\ntwice for Best Remixed Recording, Non-Classical (in 2002 and 2003).\n\nFrom 1985 to 1988, he scored four Top 10 singles on the US Dance chart,\nincluding the number one hit \"I Can't Turn Around\", all released in\ncollaboration with Keith Nunnally as J.M. Silk. With \"Jack Your Body\" (number\n#25 on the U.S. ''Billboard'' Hot Dance Music/Club Play), [http://www.billboard.com/#/artist/steve-silk-hurley/chart-\nhistory/72040?f=359&g=Singles 'Steve \"Silk\" Hurley, US peak chart positions']\nRetrieved 1 December 2010 he topped the UK Singles Chart in January 1987\nas a solo artist, [http://www.chartstats.com/artistinfo.php?id=4746 'Steve\n\"Silk\" Hurley, UK peak chart positions'] Retrieved 1 December 2010 while\none of his later compositions, \"Work it Out\" from 1989, brought him his fifth\nTop 10 record on US Dance (at number #3). To date, Hurley's last charting single\n\"The Word Is Love (Say The Word)\", also known as \"Silk's Anthem of Life\" by The\nVoices of Life, peaked in 1997 at #26 in England.\n","linknr":537,"url":"Steven_Hurley","recorded":1362477674,"links":18,"instances":["cece_peniston_song","magazine","brandy_norwood_song","united_states","entertainer","producer","song","cece_peniston_song","musician","musician","cece_peniston_song","group","song","singer","music","cece_peniston_song","cece_peniston_song","band","musician"],"pdf":[],"categories":["1962 births","Living people","People from Chicago, Illinois","Musicians from Chicago, Illinois","American house musicians","American dance musicians","American electronic musicians","American record producers","American male singers","Songwriters from Illinois","American singer-songwriters","Remixers","American DJs","Club DJs|Hurley, Steve \"Silk\"","RCA Records artists","Atlantic Records artists"],"headings":["Early life","Career","Controversies","Discography","Music awards & nominations","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Steve_%22Silk%22_Hurley.jpg/220px-Steve_%22Silk%22_Hurley.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["work_it_out","steve_\"silk\"_hurley_song"],["single","music"],["madonna","entertainer"],["brandy","entertainer"],["keep_on_walkin'","cece_peniston_song"],["searchin'","cece_peniston_song"],["i'm_not_over_you","cece_peniston_song"],["nobody_else","cece_peniston_song"],["he_loves_me_2","cece_peniston_song"],["my_boo","cece_peniston_song"],["prince","musician"],["black_box","band"],["keep_on_walkin'","cece_peniston_song"],["i'm_not_over_you","cece_peniston_song"],["he_loves_me_2","cece_peniston_song"],["clubland","group"],["music_is_the_key","steve_\"silk\"_hurley_song"],["work_it_out","steve_\"silk\"_hurley_song"],["cold_world","steve_\"silk\"_hurley_